{
  "text": "T was determined by the thermal denaturation method, essentially as described by [CITATION_1] . Purified genomic DNA was diluted in standard SSC buffer to an absorbance of 0.4 at 260 nm and was dialysed overnight against 1000 volumes SSC. The DNA melting temperature was calculated by monitoring the change in absorbance at 260 nm over increasing temperatures on a spectrophotometer (model 50; Varian Cary) in combination with a Peltier thermostat-equipped accessory and an anaerobic fluorescence cuvette [2 mm61 cm (path length)] (Starna). Genomic DNA from Escherichia coli K-12 served as a standard.",
